    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nCompiling below code using `cython -3 --shared=_cython failing.pyx` fails with following traceback:\n\n```\nCompiler crash traceback from this point on:\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Visitor.py\", line 174, in _visit\n    return handler_method(obj)\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Visitor.py\", line 538, in visit_BinopNode\n    return self._visit_binop_node(node)\n           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Visitor.py\", line 556, in _visit_binop_node\n    node = self._dispatch_to_method_handler(\n        special_method_name, None, False, type_name,\n        node, None, [operand1, operand2], None)\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Visitor.py\", line 695, in _dispatch_to_method_handler\n    result = method_handler(\n        node, function, arg_list, is_unbound_method)\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Optimize.py\", line 3498, in _handle_simple_method_object___mul__\n    return self._optimise_num_binop('Multiply', node, function, args, is_unbound_method)\n           ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/home/dev/cython/Cython/Compiler/Optimize.py\", line 3601, in _optimise_num_binop\n    elif node.type.is_pyobject:\n         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'is_pyobject'\n```\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\nfrom cython cimport view\n\ndef test_generic_slicing(arg, indirect=False):\n    cdef int[::view.generic] a = arg\n    cdef int i\n    for i in range(a.shape[0]):\n        itemA = a[2 * i]\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCompilation is successful.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14.2\n\n### Cython version\n\nmaster\n\n### Additional context\n\nRegular compilation (without shared utility) of the module is successful.",
